  "full_response": "Let's Taylor expand the following function about \\( x = 0 \\) up to \\( O(x^2) \\):\n\n\\[\nf(x) = \\frac{1}{(1 - x^2)^{1/3}}\n\\]\n\n## **Step 1: General Taylor Expansion Formula**\n\nThe Taylor expansion of \\( f(x) \\) about \\( x = 0 \\) is:\n\\[\nf(x) = f(0) + f'(0)x + \\frac{1}{2} f''(0)x^2 + O(x^3)\n\\]\n\n## **Step 2: Compute \\( f(0) \\), \\( f'(x) \\), and \\( f''(x) \\)**\n\n### **a) Compute \\( f(0) \\):**\n\\[\nf(0) = \\frac{1}{(1 - 0)^{1/3}} = 1\n\\]\n\n### **b) Compute \\( f'(x) \\):**\nWe use the chain rule:\n\\[\nf(x) = (1 - x^2)^{-1/3}\n\\]\n\\[\nf'(x) = -\\frac{1}{3} (1 - x^2)^{-4/3} \\cdot \\frac{d}{dx}(1 - x^2) = -\\frac{1}{3} (1 - x^2)^{-4/3} \\cdot (-2x) = \\frac{2x}{3} (1 - x^2)^{-4/3}\n\\]\n\nSo,\n\\[\nf'(0) = \\frac{2 \\cdot 0}{3} (1 - 0)^{-4/3} = 0\n\\]\n\n### **c) Compute \\( f''(x) \\):**\nDifferentiate \\( f'(x) \\):\n\\[\nf'(x) = \\frac{2x}{3} (1 - x^2)^{-4/3}\n\\]\n\nProduct rule:\n\\[\nf''(x) = \\frac{d}{dx}\\left(\\frac{2x}{3}\\right) (1 - x^2)^{-4/3} + \\frac{2x}{3} \\cdot \\frac{d}{dx}(1 - x^2)^{-4/3}\n\\]\n\\[\n= \\frac{2}{3} (1 - x^2)^{-4/3} + \\frac{2x}{3} \\left[ -\\frac{4}{3} (1 - x^2)^{-7/3} \\cdot (-2x) \\right]\n\\]\n\\[\n= \\frac{2}{3} (1 - x^2)^{-4/3} + \\frac{2x}{3} \\cdot \\frac{8x}{3} (1 - x^2)^{-7/3}\n\\]\n\\[\n= \\frac{2}{3} (1 - x^2)^{-4/3} + \\frac{16x^2}{9} (1 - x^2)^{-7/3}\n\\]\n\nAt \\( x = 0 \\):\n\n- \\( (1 - 0)^{-4/3} = 1 \\)\n- \\( (1 - 0)^{-7/3} = 1 \\)\n- \\( x^2 = 0 \\)\n\nSo,\n\\[\nf''(0) = \\frac{2}{3} \\cdot 1 + \\frac{16 \\cdot 0}{9} \\cdot 1 = \\frac{2}{3}\n\\]\n\n## **Step 3: Put It All Together**\n\nRecall:\n\\[\nf(x) = f(0) + f'(0)x + \\frac{1}{2} f''(0) x^2\n\\]\nSo,\n\\[\nf(x) = 1 + 0 \\cdot x + \\frac{1}{2} \\left(\\frac{2}{3}\\right)x^2 + O(x^3) = 1 + \\frac{1}{3} x^2 + O(x^3)\n\\]\n\n---\n\n\\[\n\\boxed{\n\\frac{1}{(1-x^2)^{1/3}} = 1 + \\frac{1}{3} x^2 + O(x^3)\n}\n\\]\n\nConfidence: 100%",
